Note: tr is a simple, character-based transformation tool used to translate, delete, or squeeze repeated characters in a text stream.
Only basic and commonly useful examples are included here. The command has additional capabilities not covered in this section.

Translate lowercase to uppercase

tr 'a-z' 'A-Z' < file.txt

Replace spaces with underscores

tr ' ' '_' < file.txt

Delete digits

tr -d '0-9' < file.txt

Squeeze repeated spaces into one

tr -s ' ' < file.txt

Keep only alphabetic characters (delete everything else)

tr -cd 'A-Za-z' < file.txt

Translate commas to newlines (split CSV fields into one per line)

tr ',' '\n' < file.txt

Convert Windows line endings (CRLF) to Unix (LF)

tr -d '\r' < file.txt
